Actor remembered as someone who left an incredible mark on the arts industry. Fellow actors are paying tribute to Menzi Ngubane. JOHANNESBURG - Menzi Ngubane has been described as one of the best by fellow actors and tv producers. The veteran performer's family says he died from a stroke. Ngubane was among the most popular and respected South African actors, in a career that spanned decades. READ: SA mourns the death of actress Noxolo Mashaqalala He starred in some of the biggest productions in the country including Generations, Ashes to Ashes, Yizo Yizo and Isibaya. Another veteran actor, Magic Hlatshwayo, who played Ngubane's father on Kwakhala Nyonini has been reflecting on his relationship with the 56-year-old. Watch the video above